  "$comment": [
    "Golden lock preventing silent reason-code taxonomy drift.",
    "",
    "Stability contract: within a given `reason_code_version` / `verify_reason_taxonomy_version`",
    "the code set is frozen. Existing codes are append-only across versions — renaming or",
    "removing a code always requires bumping the version.",
    "",
    "Drift detection: any add/remove/rename of a code without a corresponding version bump",
    "causes `test_reason_code_golden_lock` to fail. The intent is to force every taxonomy",
    "change to be an explicit, versioned event — never a silent modification.",
    "",
    "Regeneration: To update this snapshot after a deliberate taxonomy version bump:",
    "  REASON_CODE_GOLDEN_UPDATE=1 python3.11 -m pytest sdk/python/tests/conformance/test_reason_code_golden.py -x -q",
    "",
    "The regeneration writes a new snapshot from live module state. The regenerated file",
    "must be committed alongside the version bump."
  ],
